comments: Kuzma (WAS) legally contests Jackson's (LAC) jump shot attempt.  Any "high-five" contact after the release is considered incidental.

call_type: Turnover:  Out of Bounds - Bad Pass Turn
comments: Porzingis (WAS) passes the ball out of bounds.
Morris Sr. (LAC) places his left hand on the arm of Hachimura (WAS) during the post-up attempt. Hachimura has this arm to the back of Morris Sr., and the contact from the hand placement is marginal.
Hachimura (WAS) jumps toward Morris Sr. (LAC) and lower-body contact occurs after the release, affecting his jump shot attempt.
Mann (LAC) has a legal forearm on Porzings' (WAS) body in the post, and incidental contact occurs as Porzingis passes.
Batum (LAC) legally contests the perimeter jump shot attempt by Caldwell-Pope (WAS).
Mann (LAC) is able to inbound the ball before five seconds has passed after receiving the ball from the trail official.
Porzingis (WAS) makes marginal body contact with Jackson (LAC) in the lane, which doesn't affect his ability to pass.
After communicating with the Replay Center, there is no clear and conclusive evidence to determine if the ball hit the rim. WAS commits a 24-second violation.
Batum (LAC) briefly places an arm around Porzingis (WAS) before retracting it as both players engage and separate.
Porzingis (WAS) establishes himself in a legal screening position in the path of Coffey (LAC) and absorbs the contact on the pick.
Coffey (LAC) retracts his resting arm from Porzingis' (WAS) body and legally contests the jump shot attempt.
Batum (LAC) and Satoransky (WAS) engage and separate during the rebound.
Satoransky (WAS) makes incidental contact with Jackson (LAC) as he moves toward the rebound.
Satoransky (WAS) commits a take foul on Jackson (LAC).
Jackson (LAC) commits a take foul on Smith (WAS).
Morris Sr. (LAC) legally contests the fadeaway jump shot attempt from Kuzma (WAS).
Porzingis (WAS) commits a take foul on Coffey (LAC).
